review: these have proven to be just as good as the oems that are out there weve installed hundreds of these over the years and not one defective thermal fuse also i like the fact theyre made by supcoright here in the usa actually here in nj note  of the time or very close to that these are damaged simply because the heat temperature exiting the dryer exceeded  degreesto prevent this from happening again always replace the thermostat thats located within a couple inches away possibly more from the thermal fuse these thermostats maintain the correct temp inside the dryer they are approx rated for  degrees to  degrees im talking about the average temperature once in a while it might be by a safety or high limit thermostat pretty rare for this particular thermal fuse in some cases the newer dryers dont have a thermostat to maintain the correct temperature those dryers have thermistors thats a whole other topicnextyou need to check the vent connected to the dryer and make sure theres good air flow coming out of the outer vent vent cover there are many types of external vents or some folks call them vent covers if you dont know where your dryer vent goes to outside your home i highly recommend you find someone who can locate it and check it for you a clogged or partially clogged vent can cause your dryer to take a long time to dry clothes and that also makes your dryer work much harder to get the job donebetween the thermostat allowing it to over heat or the vent causing the trouble you wont have any heat when these thermal fuses go badplease know this if the thermal fuse isnt bad and the dryer isnt heating there may be something wrong with the electronic ignition electric heater safety thermostats wiringetci hope this helped

review: i ordered these to replace the knobs on my  year old kenmore gas range made by roper  buying the brand replacements would have cost over  per knob  thats far more than the range is worth  i looked at a lot of knob reviews for different brands online before purchasing  most of them claimed that the knobs in question did not fit their range or did not fit well  guess what these did not fit on my range out of the box either  however with ingenuity and trial and error i found a work around  now the knobs are doing their job well  all you need to do is select the plastic sleeve that fits your stem the stem that protrudes from the range  when i did this and slid the knob onto the stem it would not turn since my knob must be pushed in then turned to the left to ignite the burner  if yours operates like this do what i did  i took tiny portions of a paper towel although any similar material will do and stuffed it into the knob shaft  i filled about half of it and then slid it back on the stem  success  the problem is that the stem is much shorter than the shaft so the knob slides too close to the stove to be able to push it in before turning it  hope that description makes sense and helps someone else  the only other problem is that the knobs feel like they could be slightly tighter on the stem  if that continues i plan to wrap the stem with a piece of electrical tapesome people had trouble with the circular overlays that you peel the backing from and place on the knob  its only been a couple of days but so far they are sticking  i am sure if they come loose a dose of contact cement will remedy that situation  they look nice and are functioning for a small fracdtion of what the brand knobs would have cost  i couldnt bear the thought of the knobs being worth more than the range

review: the lint eater is amazing we recently bought a house that was built in  and previously owned by an older lady so i assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned before setting up the dryer i wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safetys sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible well im glad i did the exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that i got out were shocking it seemed like every time i ran the linteater through line it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff when i first hooked up the shop vac inside the house and went out to the vent exit there was almost zero air getting sucked in the wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and i had to keep going inside to clean it out after all was said and done my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new glad i spent the money on this producthelpful tip  when i started i just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line its way too unwieldy this way and every time you hit the power on the drill the rods get kinked and knotted up because theyre so flexible start with one and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line add another repeat as necessary and youll have a much easier time

review: im not a hvac professional but i am a scientificallyminded home owner ive been curious as to how different actions affect the humidity in our pool room among other things i have no idea if this meter is correctly calibrated or not and the manual doesnt talk about how to check this or calibrate it however i strongly suspect this is more accurate than anything i currently have i mainly used the meter to check how an action changed the humidity or temperature in a room which it appeared to do just finethe meter displays three different temperature points of the air surrounding the meters sensor ambient wet bulb and dew point the meter has buttons that allow you to hold save andor recall data it also has a min max avg function the directions are brief but i was able to use all these functions without a problem the meter is powered by  aaa batteries there is a power onoff button but the meter will also automatically turn off after  minutes there is a button to turn on and off a display backlight the meter has a belt clipthe display was large enough to read easily it quickly arrived at the reading about  seconds to stabilize unless in an area of air movement the meter is for indoor use only the manual warns to extend sensor life keep the sensors protective shutter closed whenever the meter is not in use there are no further directions about this shutter but i cant find one despite the picture its possible im overlooking the obvious but perhaps the obvious is that there isnt oneid recommend reading the reviews by professionals from the description i read to decide to review this or not id assumed it was around  and of professional quality rather than an actual professional meter id normally have left this to inthatprofession reviewers as i have no way to compare this to similar meters on the market nor can i comment on if the pricing is reasonable i apologize for that lack in my review

review: the lint eater is amazing we recently bought a house that was built in  and previously owned by an older lady so i assumed the dryer vent had never been cleaned before setting up the dryer i wanted to give the vent line a thorough cleaning for safetys sake and to help the dryer run as efficiently as possible well im glad i did the exterior cover on the vent had been gone for some time and the amount of leaves and pine needles plus lint wads that i got out were shocking it seemed like every time i ran the linteater through line it dislodged another fistsized wad of stuff when i first hooked up the shop vac inside the house and went out to the vent exit there was almost zero air getting sucked in the wads were so huge that they kept stopping up my shop vac hose and i had to keep going inside to clean it out after all was said and done my vent line is freeflowing and working as good as new glad i spent the money on this producthelpful tip  when i started i just jammed all of the rods together and tried to work it into the vent line its way too unwieldy this way and every time you hit the power on the drill the rods get kinked and knotted up because theyre so flexible start with one and when that one gets most of the way into the vent line add another repeat as necessary and youll have a much easier time

review: update  months later and the applied rerack is cracking its back to rusting you can see in my original review that i very diligently applied this stuff unfortunately it didnt last feel like i just wasted my time with my original applicationoriginal reviewjust finished repairing my dishwasher racks with this stuff you would be surprised at how much of this bottle you end up using although i guess that depends on how rusted your racks area few words of advise use a dremel type tool with wire brush and sanding attachments it is much easier to remove the rust also take your time and apply thin coats it becomes a longer process but it will be worth it in the long runmy overall process was as followsusing a dremel type rotary tool with a wire brush i removed the bulk of rust for those parts where i couldnt quite get all the rust and see bare metal i switched to a sanding attachment i then took some fine sand paper to smooth things out again the sand paper was difficult to get into the tight small spaces but did the best i could this is where i realize it would have been a lot tougher if i had to use sand paper from the startafter all the rust was removed and areas were sanded smooth i took some alcohol swaps and cleaned the areas i let that dry and then began painting i used very thin layers w  mins in between as mentioned in instructions on the bottle i probably did about  layers in total by the  layer i started to lay it on a little thicker than previously at this point there was no metal color showing through and i know i was just applying paint over paintafter all was said and done i probably used about  of the bottle i guess the size is about right since i now have a little left over for touch ups down the roadonly time will tell how it holds up in the end but it looks solid after  hrs drying

review: this review is for gardus  linteater  rotary dryer vent cleaning systemweve been paying  per visit for the service guy from the appliance store to come every  months and clean the flexible duct thats routed in a less than optimal manner due to location and a variety of road blocks from the dryer to the outside wallwe knew the time was coming for a cleaning when clothes didnt dry very well and right near the end when it really needed cleaning there would actually be water on the floor under the dryeri had to use some vacation days or lose them and was recently at home for the first time when he came i watched the process and thought i should be doing this if thats all it isi did my research linteater is pretty clearly the way to go and made my purchase youve got to love amazon primelike with any product you have weigh the number of positive reviews against the handful of bad ones the bad reviews are likely from people who are mechanically challenged or didnt read the manual or watch youtube videos to get an idea of how the process worksthe pictures of the twisted rod someone had one of more of these speed too high clutch too high or didnt use a clutched drill at all pushed against an impassable bend or obstruction on the vent pipedisconnected or broke in the vent pipe the rods cant come apart if you run the drill only clockwise thats simple physics they simply cant come apart if you use clockwise only the brush head broke or stripped out is going to be like the twisted rod speed too high clutch too high or didnt use a clutched drill at all pushed against an impassable bend or obstruction on the vent pipe clockwise only for both going into and back out of the vent tube my cordless drill is a ridgid model   the clutch goes from  to  it has a switch marked    for overall speed i set the clutch to four and the speed to one youre not drilling holes or driving screws youre not going as hard and fast as you can slow and easy wins this particular race i put red loctite thread locker on the threads attaching the rotary brush head to the rod and to the set screw as i added each section i tightened them against each other with a pair of pliers on each section then i wrapped electrical tape a couple times around the joined sections this is all just common sense insurance against disaster the female ends of the rod that go into the drill chuck arent knurled but i had no problem with them spinning in the chuck slow speed and minimal torque are probably why this was not an issuenote i didnt think id need the extra rod extensions but i do and came back to order them to get this done for now i had to do half from inside the house and half from outside inside the house vent pipe disconnected from the dryer i used the vent insert in the vent pipe end with a ridgid  shop vac and the cleaning tool rod through the provided hole in the insert this worked fantastically well i had to clean the vac filter a couple times due to all the lint outside the house i didnt bother with the vacuum figuring the birds would get whatever lint they found or the elements would just break it down pretty quickly turn the dryer on to blow out the loosened lint as you clean the pipe wear googles or something to keep the lint dust out of your eyes and off you go
product: gardus  linteater rotary dryer vent cleaning system

review: general electric  refrigerator door seal is oem replacement and fit perfectly  laid the seal out flat like they recommended for  day before installing it was packed very well and didnt have any kinks it was folded nicely with loops not folds some people suggest soaking the seal in a hot bathtub of water or put it in the dryer for  min or so i didnt need toremoved door laid flat and removed the old seal by prying up with a putty knife or a screwdriver dont pry down hard and damage the edge of the door cleaned the groove with a brass toothbrush it had a little rust on the bottom spread a little dish soap on the back of the seal to help it slide in the groove on the door best to start in a corner work your way around and press hard to snap it in tap lightly with a rubber mallet if necessary you can feel it snap into the groove check by grabbing the seal and pulling up it should be trapped in the groove especially check the corners make sure they are snapped in and the corner is exactly on the corner of the groove you can snap in two corners then press in the seal in between that way it wont be over stretched in between in case you were pulling on the rubber as you put it in clean the mating surface on the refrigerator then rehang the door i sprayed some silicone spray on a rag and wiped some on the seal and mating surface close the door and check for gaps all the way around if there is a gap heat it with a hair dryer until the rubber is soft enough to let the magnet in the seal stick to the refrigerator edge

review: important  follow the directions and remember clockwise clockwise clockwise youll understand when you see it our home is  years old and weve lived in it for  of those  years we have never cleaned the dryer ducts and were certain the previous owners wouldve had no need to do so our washer went out a week ago and so we decided to replace the dryer as well the dryer had never been moved in  years and when i went to unhook it i was amazed that the connecting pipe was almost completely clogged with lint we clean our dryer lint collector every time we use it so it got me to thinking  if theres this much lint in the connecting pipe how much lint is in the main pipe that i cant see so in anticipation of getting a new washer and dryer set i decided to look into ways of checking into this and came across this productour vent pipe is  feet long and a  degree bend  the way down well thats where this awesome tool comes in i was a bit nervous about it until i got it this thing is made very well and i had no issues with it at all i followed the directions and made sure that i   duct taped the joints  made sure my drill was set to clockwise  went slow and steady and didnt force anything the directions are very important cause if you do not follow them you could find yourself in trouble i recommend that you have a  gallon shop vac with the  hose to help you with this job the vac will help in declogging the pipe by sucking the lint as you loosen it i could not believe how much lint came out of our pipes i had to unclog the vac hose like  times because there was so much volume amazing to think that there was so much lint that it clogged up my  gallon pro shop vac  times the main thing is to go slow theres no need to put your drill on high if you dont have a variable speed drill  i recommend you get one you may get yourself into trouble if your drill only runs in super fast mode because should you run into a snag you could break the rods inside your duct can you imagine that therefore have the right tools for the job and follow the directions to the letter cause you dont want that to happendue to our  foot run i bought  kits rather than buy the extention set because to me for a few bucks more why not have extra brushes etc too the tool assembles with ease and i loved the shop vac attachment tool it came with it made this job sooooooo much easierbottom line   i love this tool it did exactly what i wanted it to do and it did it with ease and sure beat paying someone to do it i was completely done in about  hr for a  foot pipe and i have more airflow from our dryer than ever before take a look at some of the pics some people have posted with their lint because this is exactly what i experienced i removed approx  pounds of lint which is a considerable amount when you think about it our pipes are clean and i can relax in the knowledge that weve increased the life of our new dryer exponentially and removed the risk for a duct fire totally worth every cent to buy this tool in my book

review: we bought this kit to replace a broken door balance link string  this kit containing two links and two improved design guide pulleys was actually less expensive than a single link string  the improved design of the guide bracket uses a pulley at the bottom pulley and the top guide the oem had a pulley on the bottom and a fixed guide at the top  seems like a good idea right  i thought so too  actually this pulley at the top that is intended to reduce friction of the string sliding on the oem fixed guide squeaks unbearably loud when the tensioned string puts pressure on it and the plastic pulley rotates on its plastic shaft  another reviewer actually posted a video review showing how loud it is  i didnt believe them and now am sorry i didnt  it really is that loud  without pressure on the pulley it spins smoothly freely and silently but add the pressure of the tensioned door balance string and wow does the plasticonplastic rotation make a terribly loud noise  whats really odd is that the bottom pulley spins smoothly freely and silently even with the pressure on it  and its the same as the top pulley  cant figure it outcombine this with the fact that although this item is supposed to be compatible with our dishwasher model kitchenaid   it is not  the string is  inches shorter than the oem  thats nearly   this is not an exaggeration  i even moved the pulley to the closest setting gaining about  inch and it was still too much tension on the spring  i feared it would fly off at any second  and decided not to chance it  save your time and headaches and do not try to use this kit with a kitchenaid dishwasher  we are back to square one and have to live with a heavy dooras for seneca river trading i have nothing bad to say about them  they shipped fast and safely  i have contacted them and am waiting to hear on a resolution  hopefully they come through  so in a nutshell i have no complaints at this time with seneca river trading just with the item  do not use on a kitchenaid

review: i was wondering how long the upper rack adjusters would last on my whirlpoolmade kenmore dishwasher after comparing them to my moms older kenmore dw which was also made by whirlpool  i got my answer last month   years for me  a littler research online revealed that the breakage of this part is a huge problem  the achilles heel of the original parts design is the dainty wheel axles that are part of the plastic mold of the adjusters bracket  over time in the harsh dw environment these pieces which have to bear the weight of the dishes in the upper rack become brittle and eventually break  its not a matter of if it will break but rather when  shame on whirlpool for putting such garbage on consumersluckily i happened upon a video that showed this upgraded adjuster kit which really is very similar if not the same as the adjuster used prior to the one that came in the machine  there were a few helpful videos that show how to remove the old adjusters and put on the new ones  its a rather easy lowcost fix and anyone can do it without incurring the costs of a repairman  there is absolutely no reason to buy the original adjusters which are virtually the same price as this one  they really need to stop selling the old one so that unwary consumers dont waste money on themthe dishwasher is back to working as normal  actually its better than when new as the upper rack used to squeal like an oiled pig at a county fair from when it was practically new  the wheels of the new adjuster roll much more smoothly in the tracks without all the racket  the parts of this adjuster are notably heavier than the original ones as the brackets are constructed of heavy gauge metal  my moms machine is  years old and never had any issues so i believe this new adjuster will last the life of the machine without further complaint  if i were to have anything negative to say its that this adjuster intrudes slightly more into the rack  so i have to place smaller glasses next to it than before  obviously this is a minor nit but something i immediately noticed
product: whirlpool  rack  black

review: anyone who thinks they dont have a problem with lint should look at these pictures  my house is only  years old and this is what came out of our vent  that doesnt even include what was cleaned out from our dryer filter and what was in just the dryer unit  this product is very easy to use  i definitely suggest taping each junction to make sure they dont separate in the vent  i broke my cleaning into  cleanings fist cleaning was with just the brush and the first extension  after ensuring that section is clean i added the second and so forth until the brush came out clean  given the length of the brush with all four sections i found it easier to have another set of hands guide the brush into the vent while the other set was operating the drilli noticed that when i turned the dryer back on there was some lint that was dislodged and blew out the outside vent opening  unfortunately in my case some lodged between the slats and is keeping the vent opening from fully closing  i will be making a trip up my ladder once the ground dries a little so i can remove those pieces  a little price to pay for a clean vent

review: first of all this is something you dont want to mickey mouse  i made this mod for my daughters gas dryer and safety was my top concern  i found the recommended procedure difficult  there are sharp edges and didnt see how one could get a good seal with the duct tape by reaching through the holes in the dryer side and back  regarding the kit itself the piece that connects to the blower outlet and the  degree piece fit well  however the piece that goes from the  degree and out the side of the dryer was a loose fit and when pushed firmly into the  degree piece ends up being too short  the duct ends up being flush with the side of the dryer  because of the difficulty and danger of the recommended procedure and because the dryer needed a cleaning anyway i opted to disassemble the dryer removing the front and drum  more work but much less frustration  im glad i did because there was quite a bit of lint inside and i was able to assemble and tape the duct work securely  with the drum out you can easily assemble and tape the three pieces of duct work together and install it as one piece  but test fit the duct work before taping  as i mentioned the piece of duct that came with the kit that is supposed to go out the side of the dryer was too short  i decided to cut the original rear duct piece and use that which worked perfectly  tip  much easier to cut the duct work with tin snips than hacksaw  obviously you need real duct tape the shiny stuff  to complete the job i had ordered a pair of good clamps whirlpool vent clamps and flexible dryer duct dundas jafine proflex from amazon  in summary if you are determined to do the side vent conversion then despite the high price and short duct piece i think you should get the kit since it allows the duct to be secured to the dryer frame with a screw and you end up with a safe dryer and peace of mind

review: we have  foot of solid dryer vent pipe ending in  rightangles before going through the floor into the flexible dryervent hose coming from the dryer  i cant get behind the dryer without moving both the washer and dryer and they are heavy  so being lazy i decided to clean the vent from the outside of the house inward  i didnt use a vacuum cleaner or a blower or suction of any kind  i did tighten each section of tubing with pliers and taped them  i threaded all  foot of tubing with the brush on the end into the outside vent and then backed it out  i got a good amount of lint clods out  then i turned on the dryer to blow everything out  i got no air coming out at all  my fear had come true i had forced gobs of lint into the rightangles at the end of the run  i still didnt want to move that washer and dryer so i figured id try one other thing use the clodbuster attachment  now im really getting lazy so i tightened each tubing section by hand no pliers and didnt use tape  i pushed all  foot of tubing into the vent until i hit some resistance and then turned the tubing by hand too lazy to hook the drill up  then i pulled it all out and there wasnt any lint at all that came out so now im resigned to having to move the washer and dryer but before i do i figured i might as well turn the dryer on and see what happens  lots of lint clods blew out and kept coming out for about  seconds  ive attached pictures of it  im really happy with this product and if it worked for me with all the shortcuts i took it will probably work great for you  as a point of reference we built this house five years ago and this is the first time i ever cleaned the vent  a load of ten bath towels used to take  minutes to dry lately its been taking  to  hours so i knew i couldnt put cleaning the pipe off any longer

review: i bought this last october and finally got around to cleaning our  dryer duct run its just not the type of thing thats at the top of your list like wow should i go see a movie or clean our dryer duct however our dryer was drying slower and slower and i knew it was a task that i needed to tackle so i read the very long instruction book for this and began my work the instructions really need to be rewritten and simplified my sony tv has a smaller instruction manual but i do appreciate the manufacturers thoroughness for those of you with short attention spans heres my quick start guide screw the rods together and use electrical or duct tape to reinforce the joints to keep them from unscrewing during your work stick one end of rod in your drill and set the clutch pretty close to the lowest or second lowest setting then increase power if you need it attached brush to other end of rod with supplied key wrench  allen wrench and tighten make sure your drill is on clockwise  not reverse  mode or else the rods will unscrew inside your duct and youre screwed read  again turn dryer on air mode and then insert the brush in the pipe outside and begin spinning it by activating the drill push it in about a foot then pull it out and watch the lint fly then push it in  feet and pull it out and watch the lint fly then  feet etc marvel at how much lint came out marvel at how fast your dryer is and come write a review here wash the clothes you were wearing when you did this because they are now covered in linthope this helps its a quick job and well worth it the trouble

review: this worked fine for me on my  dryer  yes the printed instructions were not quite up to date with this newer model but with that and the youtube videos i had watched it was no trouble  i did try to do the replacement without removing the front bulkhead and drum  i could remove the existing duct tube using a ratchet and socket to remove the sheet metal screw  the problem was getting the new vent tubes into the dryer through either the front or the new side hole  just did not see a way to be able to get the tubes with the hose clamps installed through either opening  i also wanted to put some foil tape on the front connection where the sheet metal screw attachesso i took every thing off the front and removed the drum  it is a little difficult to get the drum belt off the tension pulley from the front  but watching the youtube videos helped just sat in front reached my left hand in on the lower left of the drum and found the tension pulley  reached my right hand in on the lower right side of the drum  you cannot see what you are doing but with the left hand grab the pulley and pull it to the left to release the tension and with the right hand pull the belt toward the back of the dryer off the pulley  release the pulley and pull the belt off the blower drive shaft toward the back of the cabinet  be sure the belt is completely clear of everything below the drum and then you can lift the drum up and out of the cabinet  then you have all the room in the world to remove the old tube and put in the new  piece tubes to vent left right or down  took me  hours

review: it is hard to believe the price on this thing from is a bargain  from amazon that is  our original was decomposing after only a few years  i am pretty sure the reason for the thing falling apart is that the part of the basket going to the back of the dishwasher is directly over part of the heat coil close enough to cause damage over time  i contacted the manufacturer for a goodwill replacement  no dice  they offered to sell me one  for edit   i want to spread the word about my experience with kitchenaid whirlpool corp on this silverware basket  before ordering here i called their contact center to ask for a goodwill replacement dishwasher is out of warranty  they said no  while shopping for the best price i saw a boatload of posts by people experiencing the same problems with warping and disintegration of the basket  i am convinced the basket problem is caused by a design defect in all of their dishwashers where the basket goes on the side  the rear of the basket sits directly over the heat coil  i believe that proximity to the heat coil causes degradation of the basket over time  i again contacted kitchenaid with this information and asked for a goodwill reimbursement for the basket i bought here  they said no  again  this is very different from my experience with an out of warranty problem on a ge refrigerator  ge took care of the problem although they were not obligated to do anything  kitchenaids approach is that once out of warranty the problems belong to the customers  consider that when you next shop for major appliancesedit   i must have caused whirlpool some embarrassment  they came thru with a reimbursement check and apology  still my experience with out of warranty situations has been outstanding with ge not so much with whirlpool

review: i have one of these stonetopped grills but i didnt get it from amazon none the less i will review this product for the sake of others considering itdoes it brown meat hell yes if you try to brown meat and fail its because the stone wasnt hot enough when you put the meat on the stone has a very high heat capacity and takes a while to get searing hot but once its hot it will brown if not blacken meat easily the stone takes a minute or two to preheat make sure you thoroughly oil the stone when you preheat the stone failure to oil the stone will make food stick to it the stone may actually have to be seasoned before use i dont know mine came in a box covered in japanese text which i cant readis it easy to clean absolutely not i used mine for korean barbecue korean marinades tend to contain sugar fruit juices or malt syrup all of these ingredients will char and leave your grill topper caked with carbon do not wash the grill with soap the stone is porous and is meant to be scraped clean soap will get into the pores and ruin the flavor of subsequent meals cooked on it repeated use will season the stone until its blackened like an old cast iron pan rinse the cooking surface under hot water and scrub with a coarse stiff brush a few times to get the loose stuff off then and scrape any charred junk off using either a razor blade topped scraper or a utility blade the one biggest drawback of this thing is the difficulty of cleaning itif the difficulty of cleaning is not worth the extra heat retention of the stone this product is not going to be worth it for you if you absolutely must have convenience get one of those nonstick coated grill toppersnow i must add that if you heat your stone too quickly it might develop cracks so preheat on medium or mediumlow rather than blasting it on high mine still works but it had visible cracks going through it after the first use where i foolishly heated it on full blast the outer metal portion holds it together such that the cracks arent really a big deal but i imagine that after repeated use a cracked stone might fall apart eventuallyone more thing this device is not meant to be used on the stove top the stoves ive tried it on dont fit well if it doesnt fit well it can shift around it fits best on one of those portable butane canister fueled burners commonly sold in asian markets the idea is that you have this thing going at the table and you cook your meats at the table korean barbecue style

review: i bought this last october and finally got around to cleaning our  dryer duct run its just not the type of thing thats at the top of your list like wow should i go see a movie or clean our dryer duct however our dryer was drying slower and slower and i knew it was a task that i needed to tackle so i read the very long instruction book for this and began my work the instructions really need to be rewritten and simplified my sony tv has a smaller instruction manual but i do appreciate the manufacturers thoroughness for those of you with short attention spans heres my quick start guide screw the rods together and use electrical or duct tape to reinforce the joints to keep them from unscrewing during your work stick one end of rod in your drill and set the clutch pretty close to the lowest or second lowest setting then increase power if you need it attached brush to other end of rod with supplied key wrench  allen wrench and tighten make sure your drill is on clockwise  not reverse  mode or else the rods will unscrew inside your duct and youre screwed read  again turn dryer on air mode and then insert the brush in the pipe outside and begin spinning it by activating the drill push it in about a foot then pull it out and watch the lint fly then push it in  feet and pull it out and watch the lint fly then  feet etc marvel at how much lint came out marvel at how fast your dryer is and come write a review here wash the clothes you were wearing when you did this because they are now covered in linthope this helps its a quick job and well worth it the trouble

review: this works as expected and the price is great compared to the local hardware store but i knocked off a star for the short service life  this is the  replacement  total in  yearsits also energy intensive roughly     the entire time the oven burner is on vs spark ignition that might spike  for a few seconds thats especially problematic if you ever have a power outage and need to run the oven off a  transducer with an extension cord unfortunately mine is only  max discovered the oven needed more than that the hard way its also problematic for anyone running on solar with batteries or a smaller generator thatll brown out if the oven burner and fridge compressor are on at the same time i think its more a fault in the oven model design than the oven ignitor itself really there is no reason it couldnt use a pilot lite for the oven session from when a temperature is set until its turned off so the glow plug is only on for a few minutes i will never get a stove with this glow plug mechanism again but its not bad enough to replace the oven earlytip recognize the signs of glow plug failure and buy a replacement ignitor before you need it check for a slight decrease in glow plug brightness over time from bright yellow to yelloworange to dull orange increasingly longer burner ignition delays despite the plug glowing dully along with difficulty maintaining temperature and maybe small spot discoloration in the glow plug element when cold at what will become the point of failure when it burns out its hard to guesstimate but when those issues start to become noticeable expect ignitor failure within a couple months of regular daily use though a dull orange glow with failure to maintain temp is probably closer to a week leftanother tip rtfm really read the service manual its not long nor particularly complicated but there are some nonobvious quirks and some differences between oven models that use these ignitors google your oven make model and service manual pdfupdate   ignitor service life from a few days after last order on september   for  until august    star for poor quality checked alternatives none look better ordered another replacement for  this failure was unexpected most of the heating element looks fine but theres a greywhite spot with slight deformation there was no noticeable decrease in brightness or temperature control tried to stick a multimeter probe in there to pick up line voltage but only managed to break the element did register line voltage at the plug theres a tiny chance its not the element

that you follow the directions the thing should never be full to the top or it doesnt work right ive found that a large load when measured correctly makes it only look about half full its a very sturdy little thing but i can see where constantly putting more of a load in it then it was made for would break it fairly quickly ive had and been using mine for over a month now and havent had a single structural problem with it sometimes you have to loosen the top screw on the lid to make sure the lid makes proper contact or it can come off but as long as you follow the instructions that hasnt been a problem i was afraid with all of the other reviews on here that it would leak around the lid not even a drop as long as its put on correctly i love the creativeness of the drain release all in all its a great product for anyone looking for a way not to have to go the the laundry mat constantly its not electric it wont spin the water out of your clothes and it wont do much for getting your clothes clean if youre expecting some miracle stain remover thatll somehow do more then a front loading washer or if you over load it but if youre looking for an efficient laundry alternative review: these are good for the pricethe product can be made great with modification  the included and preapplied tape is highstrength but its just not going to cut it for this purpose  no sticky tape will  i wish they would have no preapplied it so that i could have used it for some other purpose  not a big deal i still sort of used itfirst thing i did was cut out and remove most of the tape  i only left a half inch or so border  i then scored the bare plastic where the tape is now removed with a knife  mark and tape the rectangle where you will be attaching this  score or scuff it and clean with alcohol pads  get yourself some  minute or longer cure epoxy  mix it fill in the the detaped and scored space on the pads with epoxy  peel off the tape label  press and hold the pad to the surface of the fridge or whatever that you previously marked and taped off  the sticky tape ends up helping because it will hold it in place well while the epoxy dries and will also prevent it from leaking  wait the recommend time for cure of epoxy  when cured these will now truly be permanently attached and secure  for the stuff i used that was  hoursusing this method these are ugh never coming offever  you can lift the whole mini fridge full of stuff using this product and there is no way these are coming off  the beauty with this product is that if i ever decide to repurpose the fridge and not need to lock it anymore its not a big deal  the cable part is removable and only the bases will remain  you can hang a bottle opener or whatever from it  basically you really cant go wrong by truly permanently installing thesei would buy this again

review: marvelous  weve triedtested several different devices for indooroutdoor temperature  humidity see my other reviews and this one stands out among them for its features especially ease of use ease of viewing and having the right info in the right placethe plussesits easy to read from a distance it properly puts temperature first then humidity includes a barometer and a graph of pressure for the past  hours so you can see if weather is getting fairer or not and has a moon phase display which is great for those who enjoy stargazingyou can also cycle the  graph through for indooroutdoor temperature and humidity toowe got this one because it has humidity calibration you can alter the display  a certain amount  however weve found both temp and humidity quite accurate  that was gauged by comparing it to a set of regular thermometers and other gauges and to itself  you put the sensor next to the device indoors and see if the indooroutdoor readings matchthe backlit colors are great too giving one a feel for the outside temperature by color codeone big plus this operates off both electricity and battery  best to leave it plugged in  the cord is long enough to put it on a tablea pro and a connow the display is bright  thats great for seeing and reading it but at night the light is almost blindingly bright so much so that youll think someone has left a light on in the room its in  ok no problem as the top button can be pressed to turn off the light then in the morning you can turn it on againa negativehowever pressing that top button takes a fair amount of pressure and you have to hold it down for a couple of seconds to turn the display on more than momentarily  this worked fine for us until this morning when the kickstand broke off and the device slid off the table and crashed to the floor  turns out that the kickstand is attached to the back only with two tiny plastic pieces that are easily broken offits a real shame as it means the unit can no longer be propped up on its own for viewing  we had a spare inexpensive plastic minieasel that works though it looks poor aestheticallythe moral of this story is to use  hands to turn on the backlight one to hold the unit and the other to press the top button  otherwise the pressure is transmitted directly to the kickstand and it will eventually break off as it did to usin any event other than that it is a good product and now occupies the central place in our corral of indooroutdoor devices

review: when i first bought this cook top i gave it a five star review after waiting years for a new cook top i was so happy to have five burners with a griddle a fast boil feature and a slow simmer feature i was on top of the world  sadly within a couple of months of using this cook top the valves became very hard to turn one morning as i happily began to heat the griddle to make pancakes one of the knobs snapped off because it was so difficult to turn  i called for service and was greeted by a very unfriendly repair man after diagnosing the defective valve and ordering parts  the repairman returned in about a week or so with the wrong valvea new repairman came out a second time with the correct valve after another week or so had gone by  imagine your shiny new cook top broken while you wait for all of thiswithin a couple of months the valves became difficult to turn   once again the knobs which are plastic began to snap off simply from turning on the heat  we now have  knobs out of five that arent broken that we move back and forth to turn on the burnersonce again i called for service  i said i am done with this cooktop  i spent a fortune on this i want to exchange it for a new one i havent had this one year and it has been a problem from the starti was told by a ge rep they would not exchange our cook top but they would send out a repair manok i said send a different company i cannot deal with that first company you sent herethey sent out a different repairman this time from a great company i recognized as being in our area for at least  yearsour technician was very polite i told him our problem and he ordered the parts again  that was about two weeks ago  now we have our daughter her husband and their  little ones with us so there is a lot of cooking going review: so ill throw this out there your mileage may vary all and all it isnt a bad little beverage center for the price but there is the potential for some pain pointsthe first unit we received cooled pretty well and got a little frosty around the heat exchanger which turned out to be its death rattle no more than  hours after we plugged the unit in it was dead normally i ignore the little dont return to store fliers that the manufacturers bundle with small appliances but i decided to give danby the benefit of the doubt and called in to the customer support after about  minutes of conversation i was told there wasnt really any troubleshooting steps and to return it to amazon which amazon promptly shipped out a  unitim on my second unit and the danby seems to be doing dandy alert pun warning what i noticed with the second unit seems to have been echoed here in several comments at some point danby must have implemented an engineering change and a packaging change the second unit not only had different packaging with more padding around the compressor but the refrigerant lines were tucked in a little better and seemed to be crimped better as well something that should have keyed me off on the first one i can only guess that my initial unit may have had a loss of refrigerant at some point i also noticed this one is slightly louder not by much than the first unit as wellperformance wise the  isnt bad its fairly quiet compared to my full sized french door refrigerator the seals are good it looks great and it seems to get pretty chilly granted it is not the   degrees of my dedicated refrigerator but mine has gotten down to the low   without any adjustment from the factory setting  i may crank it to max to see what happens i do however wish they had used a cool white led bulb instead of the generic incandescent though either way its worth the price i paid for it  initial issues aside

review: first of all let me start by sayin that this heat keeper might not be for everyone  it all depends on your type of drier your homes layout and your geographical locationplease do yourself a favor and follow the safety instructions  do  not use with a gas dryerwe are currently using this in a small rental home with a crappy heater that dries the already dry new mexico winter air  it was a nobrainer to use the warm moist air into the house to help heat it and increase the humidity to comfortable levelsit is the first unit that weve ever purchased and i really dont regret it at allthis unit is extremely flimsy and falling apart when you receive it  however it does not necessarily detract from its usefulness since once installed it is sturdy enough to not fall apart  we havent had any issues with itthe vent in this house is already an exposed pipe going through the laundry room and is held up by brackets i just made sure that this unit was next to one of the brackets and added a second one  however if it had its own way of being held up it would be much betteralso the two clamps that are included in the kit are a joke and should just be tossed  get yourself a couple of metal clamps that you can adjust better with a screwdriver and youll thank yourself laterthe round lint trap is easy to pull on and off an important feature due to the fact that the mesh is not fine enough to use as is and plenty of lint escapes into the housewe actually like the filter mesh the way it is right now better because we only use it as a filter holder in the winter we take off the round lint trap put a used dryer sheet over the hole and hold it in place with the lint trap  this holds it in place while in use  once the clothes are dry we pull the lint covered dryer sheet off and replace it with the new one coming out of the dryer  it is the easiest way to keep the lint trap clean the dryer sheet catches the perfect amount of lint while letting the hot moist air in and it only it takes seconds to replace with the next one which the dryer supplies for you in the summer we take off the round lint trap put a piece of a cardboard but to the size of the trap and hold it in place with the lint trap  this is absolutely necessary otherwise you will still get hot moist air coming into your home in the heat of the summer  yes the flap is not perfect but who cares it is good enough for us

review: i purchased this product in preparation for a new dryer i figured that after i had noticed birds nesting in my exterior vent opening i should give my duct a good cleaningi am very glad i did the operation of the product is simpledo be sure to note the instruction regarding not reversing the drill when pulling the cleaner from the vent when done cleaning just leave it in the normal position as if you were driving a screw reversing the drill could cause the threaded joint fittings to come apart the next important thing to note as others have is that you need to addremove the links one at a time so that you dont have anymore than one or   not in the vent if you have too many pieces together and not inserted in the vent it will whip around and damage the rod i learned that the hard way but i blame it on myselfon to the operationresult i was blown away with the amount of straw and grass occluding my dryer vent at the exterior where the birds were once i cleared that obstruction i pulled tons of dryer lint out of the duct i was astounded at how much crud was in there and preventing my dryer from working properly as well as the potential for a dryer fire this is a product that does what it says it will do and is well worth the money

review: originally the drain beneath the freezer section had a rubber duck bill outlet that was supposed to open to allow water out and close so as not to allow moist air in fail   the rubber valve got sticky and given enough time permanently shut causing water to back up and first run over the drain pan in the freezer second into the bottom of the freezer and then third out the door and onto the floordont cheap out and just clean the duck bill value or youll be back at it again in a year order the right part  then start by taking front door off freezer loosen  screws and lift then remove  baskets remove the  screws that hold back panel on you will have to pull the fan cover off there is a plastic clip bottom front of cover and there is a thermostat hiding behind the smaller plastic cover leave the thermostat dangle once you expose the coil get a air dryer and defrost the drip pan and area below the drip pan leave it disassembled until you do the backside workoption if you dont want to pull off the back panel you can let it defrost by itself but itll take a day ice melts slowly and theres food in your refrigerator so whats easier move all the food or remove the panel i say pull the panelnext pull out the refrigerator and open up the lower back unplug the water solenoid power and move the power cord there is a slide tube that carries water from the drain hole to an evaporator pan and at the top the infamous duck bill rubber valve once you pull it off water should flow out and into the evaporator pan something should drip out and if not you may not have defrosted all the ice which is why i suggest dont put freezer section back until you have water flowing out the drain holeitll take about a minute to install the white expansion washer and then the new trap trap does not fit over white rubber washer easily but with enough patience it will dont skip the white washer that came with the new trap its the only thing that will keep the tube in place on top no screws needed make sure black tube flange is flush against top snap the bottom into the clip in the pan button it all back up push it back and put the freezer back together and rehang the doordifficulty  about a time it takes about  hours about  minutes as ice thaws so you can grab a beer and a tv showtools nut driver hair dryer and flashlightmost difficult part figuring out how to get freezer baskets out dont strong arm them just examine them from all angles and itll become obvious they come out easily if done right force them youre doing it wrong break them and itll cost you plus your wife will say see i told you to call someonesavings if you do it yourself having you wife stop complaining and threatening to call someone out priceless
product: whirlpool  tube drain replacement

review: i bought this to spare my back lugging laundry for myself and a very messy toddler up and down two flights of stairs every week i would dread laundry day all weekthis machine is a great tool i have it set up in my bathroom next to my bathtub i do have an extension cord that i employ because the electrical cord on the machine is not long enough to reach my bathrooms outlet i drain the water from the washer into the bathtub or wastebasket it works very well on small loads i can wash a set of queen size sheets in the machine and it gets them clean and fresh or i can wash a load with a pair of adult pants a blouse toddlers pajamas toddlers clothes from the day and my pajamas it does take a few loads to get a sense of what the right level of full isi do not use the hose provided to fill the washer because i didnt feel like trying to fight with my faucet or tub spout to hook it up i simply use the shower sprayer i already had to fill it some might complain about having to do this but its really not that big of an inconvenience i can loop a sprayer hose into the wash tub and let it fill without feeling like this product is a failure you do have to split the wash load into the spin dryer the spin dryer gets most of the water out of your clothes but there is no heat so youll have to either pop them into a dryer or hang them to dry i use a metal rack that i got from target but anything would work

review: dont waste your time replacing your cracked lid with yet another lid that will crack  the tension in the springs is too much for the plastic frame of the lidthe correct fix was recommended by kevin miller on the fixya websiteuse lid part    its a completely solid metal lid  use two hinges part   since the existing hinges wont work with the new lid  use four screws part   for mounting the new lid to the new hingesi used the above parts that kevin recommended and it worked perfectly  check my before and after photosreplacing it was easy  i simply removed the two screws on each side of the lid connecting it to the hinge  pulled the lid off  one of the hinges pulled out easily  the other i had to spray with lubricant and eventually it came outthe installation was just the reverse  slide the hinges into the holes of the lid and into the holes in the washer and then drive in the screws through the lid into the hingesbtw at one point my washer was spinning and did sound like a jet engine but it was still covered so they came and replaced the bearings  so i am good for now

review: i bought this last october and finally got around to cleaning our  dryer duct run its just not the type of thing thats at the top of your list like wow should i go see a movie or clean our dryer duct however our dryer was drying slower and slower and i knew it was a task that i needed to tackle so i read the very long instruction book for this and began my work the instructions really need to be rewritten and simplified my sony tv has a smaller instruction manual but i do appreciate the manufacturers thoroughness for those of you with short attention spans heres my quick start guide screw the rods together and use electrical or duct tape to reinforce the joints to keep them from unscrewing during your work stick one end of rod in your drill and set the clutch pretty close to the lowest or second lowest setting then increase power if you need it attached brush to other end of rod with supplied key wrench  allen wrench and tighten make sure your drill is on clockwise  not reverse  mode or else the rods will unscrew inside your duct and youre screwed read  again turn dryer on air mode and then insert the brush in the pipe outside and begin spinning it by activating the drill push it in about a foot then pull it out and watch the lint fly then push it in  feet and pull it out and watch the lint fly then  feet etc marvel at how much lint came out marvel at how fast your dryer is and come write a review here wash the clothes you were wearing when you did this because they are now covered in linthope this helps its a quick job and well worth it the trouble

review: this review is for gardus  linteater  rotary dryer vent cleaning systemweve been paying  per visit for the service guy from the appliance store to come every  months and clean the flexible duct thats routed in a less than optimal manner due to location and a variety of road blocks from the dryer to the outside wallwe knew the time was coming for a cleaning when clothes didnt dry very well and right near the end when it really needed cleaning there would actually be water on the floor under the dryeri had to use some vacation days or lose them and was recently at home for the first time when he came i watched the process and thought i should be doing this if thats all it isi did my research linteater is pretty clearly the way to go and made my purchase youve got to love amazon primelike with any product you have weigh the number of positive reviews against the handful of bad ones the bad reviews are likely from people who are mechanically challenged or didnt read the manual or watch youtube videos to get an idea of how the process worksthe pictures of the twisted rod someone had one of more of these speed too high clutch too high or didnt use a clutched drill at all pushed against an impassable bend or obstruction on the vent pipedisconnected or broke in the vent pipe the rods cant come apart if you run the drill only clockwise thats simple physics they simply cant come apart if you use clockwise only the brush head broke or stripped out is going to be like the twisted rod speed too high clutch too high or didnt use a clutched drill at all pushed against an impassable bend or obstruction on the vent pipe clockwise only for both going into and back out of the vent tube my cordless drill is a ridgid model   the clutch goes from  to  it has a switch marked    for overall speed i set the clutch to four and the speed to one youre not drilling holes or driving screws youre not going as hard and fast as you can slow and easy wins this particular race i put red loctite thread locker on the threads attaching the rotary brush head to the rod and to the set screw as i added each section i tightened them against each other with a pair of pliers on each section then i wrapped electrical tape a couple times around the joined sections this is all just common sense insurance against disaster the female ends of the rod that go into the drill chuck arent knurled but i had no problem with them spinning in the chuck slow speed and minimal torque are probably why this was not an issuenote i didnt think id need the extra rod extensions but i do and came back to order them to get this done for now i had to do half from inside the house and half from outside inside the house vent pipe disconnected from the dryer i used the vent insert in the vent pipe end with a ridgid  shop vac and the cleaning tool rod through the provided hole in the insert this worked fantastically well i had to clean the vac filter a couple times due to all the lint outside the house i didnt bother with the vacuum figuring the birds would get whatever lint they found or the elements would just break it down pretty quickly turn the dryer on to blow out the loosened lint as you clean the pipe wear googles or something to keep the lint dust out of your eyes and off you go
product: gardus  linteater rotary dryer vent cleaning system

review: i wanted to wait and use the ice maker for a while before writing a review as quite often things that start out great end up disappointing i can now give a pretty solid endorsement aside from a couple of small quibbles which i will get to i am suitably impressedour last countertop ice maker died peacefully in its sleep after a long and chilling life  it was a manual fill manual empty model and we had just gotten used to all of its faults slow poorly insulated we manually emptied the ice into a bin in the freezer and kept an ice pick handy to break it all up after a couple of months buying bags of ice we decided it was time to look into a replacementto answer a few of the questionscomplaints i have seen in other reviewsa user manual was included with  mine but the instructions could have been better i didnt have any trouble at all thoughdo follow the advice to leave it on the counter with all the doors open for a couple of hours before using itdo plan on tossing out most of the ice made the first day you have it allow lots of fresh clean water to cycle throughi do wish it had a slightly larger capacity ice storage bini have not had any trouble with the dispenser being unable to dispense the ice because of it freezing together it isnt the fastest dispenser ive seen but it works finethe water supply line you need is standard for ice makers and many water filters  od and uses a quickfit push in type connector on the back of the machine i also ran an inline water filter i picked up at home depot for a few bucks be sure to preflush the filter if you add one the first bit of water run through new filters is usually black as it washes the carbon dust offthe water is dispensed from the reservoir for the occasional glass this is nice because it means the water is probably well chilled already runoff from the ice making process and melt from the ice storage bin both go into the water reservoir but this does mean it might be a bit slow to fill more than one or two glasses back to backi do wish there were a way to adjust the volume or mute the ding tones but i havent found them obnoxious and they dont wake me at nightoverall this ice machine does what i expect from it and it does it without any trouble
product: nutrichef ice maker and dispenser  upgraded machine countertop ice dispenser ice machine w easytouch buttons get ice in  minutes produces  lbs of ice per  hours   silver

review: i bought this last october and finally got around to cleaning our  dryer duct run its just not the type of thing thats at the top of your list like wow should i go see a movie or clean our dryer duct however our dryer was drying slower and slower and i knew it was a task that i needed to tackle so i read the very long instruction book for this and began my work the instructions really need to be rewritten and simplified my sony tv has a smaller instruction manual but i do appreciate the manufacturers thoroughness for those of you with short attention spans heres my quick start guide screw the rods together and use electrical or duct tape to reinforce the joints to keep them from unscrewing during your work stick one end of rod in your drill and set the clutch pretty close to the lowest or second lowest setting then increase power if you need it attached brush to other end of rod with supplied key wrench  allen wrench and tighten make sure your drill is on clockwise  not reverse  mode or else the rods will unscrew inside your duct and youre screwed read  again turn dryer on air mode and then insert the brush in the pipe outside and begin spinning it by activating the drill push it in about a foot then pull it out and watch the lint fly then push it in  feet and pull it out and watch the lint fly then  feet etc marvel at how much lint came out marvel at how fast your dryer is and come write a review here wash the clothes you were wearing when you did this because they are now covered in linthope this helps its a quick job and well worth it the trouble

review: great product but they need to include more rods in the kit i had to buy a second set of rods and that still wasnt enough so ill end up spending  dollars on this kit which isnt terrible if you factor what you would get charged out in town but still its plastic rods with a brush attachedthats overpriced for something so simpleso enough of me complaining about it being overpriced and get to the review it works great if you arent an idiot and use common sense when using it  always clockwise again always clockwise i cant be anymore clear about this  use electrical tape or duct tape as a backup in case you screw up on number  above its a good safety measure so just do it it only takes a few seconds per rod to wrap in tape  feed one rod at a time taping each one as you go  dont force the rods if you get resistance with the drill attached if you get resistance remove the drill from the rod and using your hands wiggleshift the rods until you get past the resistance and then reconnect the drill and continue most likely if you reach resistance is likely one of two things  you have a large bend in your duct or  you have a lot of blockage if its number  start pulling the rod out with or without the drill attached if the drill remains attached remember to always spin  clockwise as youve probably hit a patch of lint clogged heavily in one area pulling the rod out will likely pull a large portion of lint youve broken loose out with the rod and brush  attachment so vacuum it up or blow it out if you have a leaf blower and then start again i didnt disconnect rods during this step but i did take my time to hand feed the rod and brush back in to ensure i didnt damage the rods  once youve reached the end of your vent start pulling your rods out the same way you went in clockwise so that you catch any debris you might have missed on the initial cleaning  i pushed the brush through  times in total from different sides of the vent since i was short a few rods and used the leaf blower  times in between to ensure i was pushing any lint to the exterior of the house never blow the leaf blower into the house only blow to the outside of the house unless you want a huge mess in your house  lastly id recommend using a face maskrespirator mask as this stuff is messy and you dont know whats growing in it i had some cheap carpentry mask but will use a better version next time i clean it as its not fun to breath in

review: great product but they need to include more rods in the kit i had to buy a second set of rods and that still wasnt enough so ill end up spending  dollars on this kit which isnt terrible if you factor what you would get charged out in town but still its plastic rods with a brush attachedthats overpriced for something so simpleso enough of me complaining about it being overpriced and get to the review it works great if you arent an idiot and use common sense when using it  always clockwise again always clockwise i cant be anymore clear about this  use electrical tape or duct tape as a backup in case you screw up on number  above its a good safety measure so just do it it only takes a few seconds per rod to wrap in tape  feed one rod at a time taping each one as you go  dont force the rods if you get resistance with the drill attached if you get resistance remove the drill from the rod and using your hands wiggleshift the rods until you get past the resistance and then reconnect the drill and continue most likely if you reach resistance is likely one of two things  you have a large bend in your duct or  you have a lot of blockage if its number  start pulling the rod out with or without the drill attached if the drill remains attached remember to always spin  clockwise as youve probably hit a patch of lint clogged heavily in one area pulling the rod out will likely pull a large portion of lint youve broken loose out with the rod and brush  attachment so vacuum it up or blow it out if you have a leaf blower and then start again i didnt disconnect rods during this step but i did take my time to hand feed the rod and brush back in to ensure i didnt damage the rods  once youve reached the end of your vent start pulling your rods out the same way you went in clockwise so that you catch any debris you might have missed on the initial cleaning  i pushed the brush through  times in total from different sides of the vent since i was short a few rods and used the leaf blower  times in between to ensure i was pushing any lint to the exterior of the house never blow the leaf blower into the house only blow to the outside of the house unless you want a huge mess in your house  lastly id recommend using a face maskrespirator mask as this stuff is messy and you dont know whats growing in it i had some cheap carpentry mask but will use a better version next time i clean it as its not fun to breath in

review: being a single parent and on a budget going to the local laundromat to wash clothes was not cost efficient at all spending over ten dollars to wash and dry a few loads of colthes and blankets was quickly adding up not to mention finding the time to get to therei bought this unit not looking for a miracle but a solution to my problem washing the clothing that my family of four had and trying to save money this product thus far is doing just thati wash at least three loads of clothes  jeans shirts socks delicates shorts and dresses and small basic house goods  towels sheets pillow cases small throw blankets twice a week using a bucket i fill my washer always making sure to check my load size and the appropriate fill line in the machine i use less liquid detergent than in a full sized washer and am sure not to use hot water depending on the load i set it to wash for a minimum of  minutes to the full  minutes i drain all the water out at the end of the cycle and then fill the unit with fresh water to rinse for at least  minutes  always be sure to set the unit back to normal  or soft after you finish drain and before you start refilling with fresh water if not the unit will spray water out from the drain hose when you start the machineone of the best aspects of the unit is the spinner i usually only place a few items in at a time and spin for  minutes the full  minutes is great for heavy items such as jeans or towels be sure they are leveled correctly so that the unit does not start becoming off balance  you will hear the sound difference when this occurs when the items come out of the spinner they are almost completely dry this makes hang drying easier or in my case placing them into my small panda dryer a quick dryi love my portable washer it hopefully will last for some time to come with proper use and care

review: i have a maytag  refrigerator which recently stopped working i decided to see if i could repair it i plugged it in with the rear cardboard panel removed and i heard the compressor start and run for a couple of seconds then quit i could also hear  sizzling noise coming from the relay mounted on the compressor a little smoke came from the area of the relaywhen i looked online for a replacement relay i figured i would replace the overload at the same time however the overload for my model is no longer available so i came across a site the indicated this part would work and other sites that said it did not fit amazon indicated it would fit so i gave it a trywhen i received this new start device i removed the original run capacitor from its mount to the left of the compressor by simply removing the screw holding it in place i then plugged the run capacitor into the  start device and it fit perfectlythe one issue i encountered was the size of the connectors the original connectors were   inch and the connectors on the new start device were   i didnt want to make any wiring modifications in case i need to revert back to using the original style relayoverload so i made up two small wiring adapters i used two short pieces of appropriate gauge stranded copper wire with a  insulated male connector on one end and a  female connector on the other end i did need to use some electrical tape to cover the back side of the  male connector that was inserted into the insulated female connector i also taped over the end of the orange wire connector that originally went to the run capacitorthe refrigerator is running well nowas an additional note i ordered this from amazon warehouse deals so my total cost to fix the refrigerator was around  which includes the   day shipping and the connectors

review: i bought this last october and finally got around to cleaning our  dryer duct run its just not the type of thing thats at the top of your list like wow should i go see a movie or clean our dryer duct however our dryer was drying slower and slower and i knew it was a task that i needed to tackle so i read the very long instruction book for this and began my work the instructions really need to be rewritten and simplified my sony tv has a smaller instruction manual but i do appreciate the manufacturers thoroughness for those of you with short attention spans heres my quick start guide screw the rods together and use electrical or duct tape to reinforce the joints to keep them from unscrewing during your work stick one end of rod in your drill and set the clutch pretty close to the lowest or second lowest setting then increase power if you need it attached brush to other end of rod with supplied key wrench  allen wrench and tighten make sure your drill is on clockwise  not reverse  mode or else the rods will unscrew inside your duct and youre screwed read  again turn dryer on air mode and then insert the brush in the pipe outside and begin spinning it by activating the drill push it in about a foot then pull it out and watch the lint fly then push it in  feet and pull it out and watch the lint fly then  feet etc marvel at how much lint came out marvel at how fast your dryer is and come write a review here wash the clothes you were wearing when you did this because they are now covered in linthope this helps its a quick job and well worth it the trouble

review: nothing superfancy to say about it  this is the real filter for the ventasonic  models of humidifiers  it easily screws right on to the upper side of the reservoirs gasketted plug for lack of a better word which in turn screws into the reservoirs fill opening  it prevents the formation of that very fine white dust that many ultrasonic humidifiers put out if you dont use a filter  the nanosilver product prevents that gross mold from growing  you still need to clean the humidifier the base more so than the reservoir but since you dont have the mold growth cleaning is easy  one filter lasts an entire heating season for methe only problem i have is that they have apparently quit making the  model which has the led display panel which i found very helpful  but for the model  and for those who still have the model  this is the filter and it is great

review: this part fits perfectly in my sink drain  in diameter the ones they sell at lowes or depot do not fit sinks made for ge disposals so this was good for that purpose it appears to be a durable part that will last a long time im sure my only contention with it thus the two star deduction is that the water doesnt flow through it well at all as many other reviewers have also stated even with the faucet turned on to half flow the water pools up in the sink and takes a long time to drain through this part which is a pain if you have a bunch of crud in the water from rinsing dishes there are little rubber skins between the grooves that go from the center hole to their individual small holes on the outer some of the little holes also have this rubber remnant its like a leftover little skin from the likely injection mold process used to make these i spent over an hour with my xacto knife cutting away these little skins and making the center hole and all the small holes a little bigger the water flows better however it still pools up a little when i have the faucet turned on full i dont want to trim more because i dont want to lose the shielding from grinding food bits in the disposal that this part is meant to provide so i guess its a happy medium perhaps a different cutout design would provide ample water flow while maintaining a good guard against flying bits while running the disposal its too bad because there doesnt seem to be any better options out there for the ge size drains

review: i purchased this drain pump to replace the one on my lg model  washing machine and it was a perfect fitin recent days i had begun getting the oe error on the display on my  year old lg washer indicating that the machine wasnt draining properly  after checking the pump filter basket and the drain tube and finding no problems i opted to spend the  on this pump rather than going out and spending a couple thousand bucks on a new set because apparently the washer and dryer have to match rolleyesi had watched a video on the web with disassembly steps for removing the front panel to get to the pump  it was fairly straightforward and was just time consuming to get everything apart and back together  the one item i struggled with a bit was getting the door boot seal retainer spring back in place had to fiddle with it a while to find a technique to get the spring in place without pulling the rubber boot out of place in the processafter a few loads of clothes im confident that this fixed my issue  and when i took the old pump apart further i found lots wet gunk on the interior area of the motor and it didnt take much force to make the impeller slip and spin on the armature shaft  i think this is likely what was happening the old motor armature was still spinning but the impeller wasnt spinning with it

review: at first appearance this thing looks cheap and flimsy and its light as a feather too so i had my doubts removing it from the box that it would do the job  it comes completely compressed so the first thing i needed to do was to stretch it out and shape it into an s exactly like the picture shows for my install  best advice here is to go very slowly dont just yank it and try to get it to stretch open uniformly rather than just in the middle or at one end  the bending part is the trickiest and here again best to work it very slowly  i found it helped putting one hand inside the tube for support while bending to keep the material from kinking too much  if you get a kink you can gently push it out a bit just dont be too aggressive or you could easily put a crack in the tube  making the end connections is easy i put  slits on the collars at each end so theyd slip over the mating vents and used worm gear clamps to hold it in place  i also used a very tiny bit of aluminum tape just to seal the small gap where i had cut the  slits a bit too long on one side some people like to put tape all the way around the connection however thats not a good idea as it makes it harder to do your annual or biannual lint inspections  finally cranked up the dryer to make sure there were no leaks and there werent so the flimsy looking product ended up making a very solid install and at a great price
